// @check
// @error-at 10:4 invalid match pattern `high` — a pattern is a member string literal or the `_` wildcard
// A pattern that is an identifier OTHER than the `_` wildcard covers nothing —
// the checker rejects it AT THE PATTERN. Silently skipping it either acted as a
// phantom wildcard (suppressing exhaustiveness for the whole match) or surfaced
// later as a misattributed "non-exhaustive match" pointing at the match head.
// The exhaustiveness check is suppressed for this match (the bad pattern is the
// root cause — no cascaded missing-member report for "b").
function f(x: "a" | "b") {
  match x {
    high => print(1),
    "a" => print(2),
  }
}
f("a")
